The paper deals with optimization and reoptimization problems in scheduling, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The use of parallel machines and the minimization of makespan are common themes in scheduling problems, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses parameterized and approximation algorithms, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
